description: This graphic novel chronicles the strange and bizarre adventures of a federal agent and his partner - hence, the name The Fed. Who, if need be, will blackmail, will intimidate and even murder to guard their secret information. In a lot of ways it is a sort of parody of the X-Files, where, in that show, Mulder and Scully fought to uncover ominous government conspiracies, in this it's just the opposite!
name: The Fed

description: In the “alternative dimension” of the 1930s, Martin, Java, Agent Diana and Angie are trying to repel an alien invasion! Who are the mysterious creatures who landed on the Earth, and what is their goal? Who’s their leader? Who is Angie’s quirky husband, and why did he suddenly disappear at Niagara Falls? Which part of the universe did Martin Mystére and Java end in, after crossing a weird hexagonal portal? Who is the mysterious GorSamsa, and what’s his role in the whole situation? And, above all, why did “Elsewhere” ask for the help of Orthon Whales, a film director and the greatest young genius in the U.S.? This year’s Almanacco also includes full-color dossiers about fanta-pulp magazines, Terry Brooks’ magic secrets and alien deities, along with everything you need to know about the “mysterious” books, movies, TV series and videogames of the year!
name: Almanacco Del Misterio 2015
